                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">What You'll Learn</h2>
                                <p>The CSS box model is essentially a box that wraps around every HTML element. It consists of: margins, borders, padding, and the actual content. The image below illustrates the box model:</p>
                                <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-100 dark:bg-white/5 my-4 flex justify-center items-center">
                                    <img class="max-w-sm" data-alt="Diagram of the CSS Box model, showing content, padding, border, and margin layers." src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aida-public/AB6AXuBO-5P0XLlFvj8VaNhpJamNGryDNdJHdbBnvQAhcZpRW1foz0-NSckrhnfyt03XUI7mCP90m2LLzLrjHrkAyYzGS_1JzweU7Pep0Uehsn6N7kBwyfeshG2vQuHcQdPBpiOxbPTZvL8OSRPK3TEJV5DdFyjpg3wE16lpp-6tpL2CSh4vwRYfcUjIuCsDhCn_k1MP09Jrf_QVPdXl7oPVDxP0t-ySJhrkfWqAfnxTOJKjwQqM7AHmfKst5dcbqELucRFF_CDNL9JmCb8" />
                                </div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Your Task</h3>
                                <p>In the interactive workspace to your right, you'll find an HTML file with a `div` element and a CSS file. Your goal is to:</p>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Add a <strong>20px</strong> padding to all sides of the box.</li>
                                    <li>Give it a solid <strong>5px</strong> blue border.</li>
                                    <li>Set a <strong>15px</strong> margin on the outside.</li>
                                </ol>
                                <p>Use the live preview to see your changes instantly. Good luck!</p>
